text.tspan: Suicide rate vs. prevalence of mental & substance use disorders, 2017
Suicide rates per 100,000 people versus rates of mental and substance use disorders per 100,000 people. This
includes depression, anxiety, bipolar, eating disorders, alcohol or drug use disorders, and schizophrenia. Suicide
deaths are underreported in many countries due to social stigma and cultural or legal concerns. This data is
adjusted for this underreporting to estimate the actual rate of suicides.
Mental and substance use disorder rate
Data source: IHME, Global Burden of Disease (2017, 2019)
Note: To allow for comparisons between countries and over time, this metric is age-standardized.
